I absolutely love how easy it is for me to create presentations and customize pre-made templates with @canva in my kindergarten classroom.
I absolutely love how easy it is for me to create slides and templates with @canva in my kindergarten classroom.
 
Creating visual directions has been a game changer and really helps my students who need visual reminders!

@thelistshowtv  interviewed me and asked me for some tips to give parents whose children’s are returning back to school after remote learning.

Things are constantly changing and I don’t have all of the answers but hopefully some of these tips are helpful to you :)

node.title: Tips For Getting Kids Ready for the Classroom

🍬🍪
The cookie jar has retired
But the candy jar is here!

And it’s obviously rainbow for my class 🤣🌈

Y’all we aren’t going to talk about the amount of extra this was… i just couldn’t see one of the first things I purchased for my house go to waste 🙃🤷🏽‍♀️

My dad and brother won’t be stealing cookies out of the cookie jar anymore but my kinders will be enjoying our rainbow jar this year 💕

Thanks @maniacsinthemiddle for inspiring me with your jolly ranchers 
.
.
.
#teachersofinstagram #iteach #classroomsetup #kindergarten

✌🏽✔️
Today was our first official day back and my second day getting my room together.

I am all moved into my new classroom, pretty much unpacked and the base of my bulletin boards are done 👏🏽🙌🏽

Tomorrow morning is filled with meetings but I’m hoping to get some more done in the afternoon.

I’m feeling really good 💕🥰

node.text:
☀️✌🏽
Thank you Summer 2021!

Tomorrow is my first official day back to work.

Today’s message at church was everything I needed to get me in the right head space for tomorrow.

I feel at peace and ready for this week!

I’m so thankful this summer!
It was everything I knew I needed.

Get your hair done,
Buy the coffee,
Take the walk,
Say no,
Do whatever you need to do to feel like the best version of you.

.

node.text:
🤎🍪
Just a girl and a gallon of cookies!

After almost 4 years (new cookies i promise lol) these cookies jars that became a staple in my kitchen are finding a new home 🤣

I will miss being asked
“How do you get them some perfect?” and
“do you even eat them?” 🤣🤣
but they will have a new home
and purpose now 🙌🏽

Any guesses on where this jar will go and what treasures it will hold?

Ps.
If you’re new here I’m not us usually this weird lol. But i did really love these jars.

node.text:
💕🙏🏽
Reminding myself that “people” will always disappoint you, but God.. He is always good.

I consider myself to be a good human. So when people do unkind, shady, malicious, deceitful and hateful things I just don’t get it.

I try to give them the benefit of the doubt. I run through the story over and over attempting to gain some clarity.

Yesterday was heavy and I still don’t understand it completely. But as my boo always tells me “it may not be for you to understand”

But what I do know is that the enemy hates to see you happy. I lived my best  life this summer and I am so grateful!And although I would love to share that joy with others and hope they would be happy for me… that’s just not reality.

So today I am making an honest effort to not allow hurt people to break me or my spirit! 

I am putting down the heaviness of these past few days, I am no longer trying to figure out “why would they do that” or “why would they think that”. I am done trying to prove who I am and who God has created me to be.

Today I will be joyful!

If yesterday was heavy, put it down!
Praying for you 💕

node.text:
💃🏽🕺🏿
Wiggle Like Me Wednesday is one of our favorite morning meeting activities.

✨I share all about this activity and my entire morning meeting routine in the @nowthatswhaticallteaching PD.✨

✔️If you are interested in learning more click the link in my bio.
🗓The sale ends tomorrow 😉💕

☀️When I decided to revamp my morning meeting time I knew I wanted it to be impactful, fun, engaging and meaningful.

🌻I also knew that I didn’t want it to take up to much time.

💛I love that we are able to talk about our feelings, share, practice mindfulness and start our day off feeling good and encouraged.

Morning meeting use to be just something I did, now it’s my favorite part of the day 🤗

💯The way you start  your morning is so important, it should be something you and your students enjoy!

#teachersofinstagram #teachersfollowteachers #iteach #morningmeeting  #nowthatswhaticallteaching  #morningroutines☀️
